msgid "Starting the XO"
msgstr ""

# 25194c3fc5554e86880ce25ccd0012f5
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:10
msgid ""
"To start the XO, press the Power button, near the lower right corner of the "
"screen. The XO takes about 30 seconds to start up."
msgstr ""

# 200d431cdec943bbbe1a2da7e19f607e
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:12
msgid ""
"If the battery needs charging, the light next to the power button glows red. "
"Plug the AC adaptor into the left side of the XO and plug the power cord "
"into an outlet if you see the red light or if the XO does not start up."
msgstr ""

# 0d70032a1cdc482b9681a8c9c81139fd
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:14
msgid ""
"If you have difficulty starting your XO, refer to the Repairing chapter for "
"ideas."
msgstr ""

# 471a90701d314ce5900203b59555b7bc
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:17
msgid "Starting for the first time"
msgstr ""

# 27fa58aa7b5b4f6184a7fdb6c027e227
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:19
msgid ""
"After you press the power button and the XO initially starts up, the XO "
"screen asks for your first name. The next time you start it, it remembers "
"your name and goes directly to the Home View. Later on you can learn how to "
"change to a nick name of your choosing."
msgstr ""

# a68053bd408843a5bcc20b17ae2c3847
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:21
msgid "Type your name."
msgstr ""

# 4405f8dd1bb341b4b390395417f058bc
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:25
msgid ""
"After you enter your name, click Next. (Use a finger on the touchpad below "
"the keyboard to move the arrow over the word \"Next\". Press the key below "
"the touchpad on the left with an \"X\" on it to \"click\".)"
msgstr ""

# 2a5e87baca70464b97565e9091e7417f
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:29
msgid ""
"Next, you see a small O on top of an X. This symbol represents you when you "
"use your XO. Use your finger on the touchpad to move the arrow over the "
"person symbol. \"Click\" this person symbol by pressing the key with an \"X"
"\" on the left below the touchpad to choose colors that you like."
msgstr ""

# f4c7301b07674de9941dccd70d762dea
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:33
msgid "After you chose your colors, click \"Done.\""
msgstr ""

# e573c4145d8a402eb1e1859eae7b0598
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:38
msgid "Putting the XO to sleep"
msgstr ""

# bb46279c23a945a782ce364287fb96e1
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:40
msgid ""
"When you are ready to stop using your XO for a while, you can put it to "
"sleep by pushing the power key you used to turn it on. The screen that "
"appears when you push the power button shows the two reasons for sleeping; "
"when you haven't been using it for a while, or when you push the power "
"button."
msgstr ""

# 4c584268c1e54805a5bb3e9aabfc4889
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:45
msgid "Shutting down the XO"
msgstr ""

# ccdedec1fb184b64b1a0353db355e371
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:47
msgid ""
"When you have finished using the computer, click over the XO icon in the "
"middle of the Home screen, and select the option Shutdown."
msgstr ""

# 6daafe2e2ee24e6ab691687ae143f4ec
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:52
msgid "Forced Shutdown"
msgstr ""

# 611e194141dc4903803b245cf15cd2d5
#: ../source/starting_the_xo.rst:54
msgid ""
"Whenever the XO becomes unresponsive to the keyboard or to the touchscreen, "
"you can make an emergency shutdown by pressing and holding the power button "
"for a few seconds. Be careful that your power button does not get \"stuck\" "
"in the down position. If it does get stuck, the XO does not detect the "
"depression of the power button, and does not turn on. If this happens, refer "
"to the Repairing chapter for information."
msgstr ""
